Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp with part-preserved symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Timotheos. The month name is occasionally found preceding that of Timotheos, but there is no close parallel.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1109)
